Emlak Konut, Garanti, TAV: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-04T07:15:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/emlak-konut-garanti-tav-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 1,722.80, or
2.9 percent, to 60,387.04 yesterday.    Emlak Konut Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (EKGYO)  :
Turkey’s biggest housing developer will buy property in Istanbul
for 225.4 million liras ($141 million) from its parent, the
government’s housing agency, known as Toki, according to a
statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange after the market closed
yesterday. Emlak Konut gained 22 kurus, or 9.3 percent, to 2.58
liras.    Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  : The Turkish bank, in
which Spain’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA is buying a
24.9 percent stake, plans to distribute 570 million liras of
dividends from 2010 profit from April 11. The bank will propose
a gross dividend of 0.13571 lira per share, equal to 0.11536
lira net, to a  shareholders’ meeting  on March 31, it said in a
statement to the bourse after the close yesterday. Garanti rose
20 kurus, or 2.9 percent, to 7.06 liras.    Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  : Exsa Export Sanayi
Mamulleri Satis & Arastirma AS, the foreign trade unit of
Turkey’s second-biggest group of companies, plans to buy a stake
of as much as 5 percent in Sabanci Holding on the bourse within
a year, Exsa said in a statement to the bourse yesterday.
Sabanci advanced 16 kurus, or 2.6 percent, to 6.44 liras.    TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS (TAVHL)  : Turkey’s biggest
airport operator said profit last year fell to 99 million liras
from 108.7 million liras in 2009, according to a statement to
the bourse after the close yesterday. The company was expected
to earn 102.3 million liras in a Bloomberg survey of 13
analysts. TAV rallied 22 kurus, or 3.5 percent, to 6.60 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
